ixed income. Direct lending tends to provide more conservative risk-return profiles than leveraged loans and high yield bonds. For investors willing to lock up capital and commit for an extended period, direct lending offers access to an asset class with appealing enhanced yield and downside mitigation. ( <a href="https://d1e00ek4ebabms.cloudfront.net/production/uploaded-files/UBS%20primer%20on%20private%20credit-d923895f-1d8a-44d2-98b4-54ded3ea9577.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">UBS</a> )</p><p> • <strong>Inside the Slow, Yet &#39;Incredible&#39; Installation of a $78,000 Tesla Solar Roof</strong> : Long Island homeowner Winka Dubbeldam describes a tedious process that in the end helped lower her electric bill while maintaining the appearance of her Cape Cod-style h ome. （ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/real-estate/tesla-solar-roof-installation-234824da" target="_blank" rel="noopener">华尔街日报</a>）</p><p> • <strong>Why This Company&#39;s Financial Crisis Threatens China&#39;s Economy</strong> : Country Garden was China&#39;s biggest real estate developer. Now it is staring down default, facing billions of dollars in losses and $200 billion in unpaid bills. （ <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/15/business/country-garden-china-property.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">纽约时报</a>）</p><p> • <strong>LK-99 isn&#39;t a superconductor — how science sleuths solved the mystery</strong> : Replications pieced together the puzzle of why the material displayed superconducting-like behaviours. （<a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-023-02585-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener">自然</a>）</p><p> • <strong>Tracking the EV battery factory construction boom across North America</strong> : Here&#39;s where the US stands on EV battery production, 1 year after the Inflation Reduction Act was signed. （ <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/08/16/tracking-the-ev-battery-factory-construction-boom-across-north-america/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TechCrunch</a> ）</p><p> • <strong>How the collapse of the ruble could impact the war in Ukraine</strong> : The Russian ruble has been declining steadily and reached a 17-month low this week, tumbling past 100 rubles to the US dollar. This gives the ruble less value than a single American cent and represents a loss of nearly 40% of its value since the beginning of the year. The ruble immediately plunged following Russia&#39;s invasion of Ukraine in February 2022. It saw an uptick at the end of that year but has been falling ever since. ( <a href="https://theweek.com/talking-point/1025830/ruble-collapse-ukraine-russia-war" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Week</a> )</p><p> • <strong>A brilliant biography of an elusive genius</strong> : Spinoza may be the master thinker to whom we owe modernity itself. • A brilliant biography of an elusive genius: ( <a href="https://thecritic.co.uk/issues/august-september-2023/a-brilliant-biography-of-an-elusive-genius/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Critic</a> )</p><p> • <strong>The Biggest Question Mark in Astronomy? You&#39;re Looking at It</strong> . Close scrutiny of a recent image from the Webb Space Telescope revealed some questionable punctuation. （ <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/08/18/science/space/question-mark-space-webb-telescope.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">纽约时报</a>）</p></blockquote><p>请务必查看我们的法律学者卡斯·桑斯坦 (Cass Sunstein) 的<a href="https://ritholtz.com/category/podcast/mib/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-web-url="http://www.bloombergview.com/topics/masters-in-business">商业硕士学位</a>，他创立并领导了哈佛法学院的行为经济学和公共政策项目。他撰写了多本书，包括畅销书《 <a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0300122233/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>助推：改善有关健康、财富和幸福的决策</em></a>》。 （与诺贝尔奖获得者理查德·塞勒合着）和《纽约时报》畅销书《 <a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0062484222/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">星球大战中的世界</a>》。他的新书是《 <a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1009400460/thebigpictu09-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener">关于决策的决策：日常生活中的实践理性</a>》。</p><div></div><p> <strong>SPAC Mergers Have Hardly Been A Guarantee Of Success In Recent Years</strong><br /> <a href="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-318579" src="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers.png" alt="" width="600" height="600" srcset="https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers.png 1198w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers-300x300.png 300w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers-1024x1024.png 1024w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers-150x150.png 150w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers-768x768.png 768w, https://ritholtz.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/spacmergers-250x250.png 250w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /></a><br /> Source: <a href="https://www.chartr.co/newsletters/2023-08-18" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chartr</a></p><p></p><p> <a class="gtrackexternal" href="https://mailchi.mp/005fb77d75b9/ritholtzreads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>在此注册我们的只读邮件列表</em></a>。</p><p></p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com/2023/08/10-monday-am-reads-399/">10 Monday AM Reads</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://ritholtz.com">The Big Picture</a> .</p> ;
